The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, May 1: The empowered group of ministers to examine the minimum area required to set up special economic zones is likely to hold its first meeting on May 10 after deferring it twice. The group, headed by defence minister Pranab Mukherjee, to review the land size issue was set up in March but has not been able to meet until now as other ministers have been busy with the Assembly polls in five states.

 New Delhi, May 1: Meeting the December 2006 schedule to conclude the Doha round of WTO talks was crucial for India, although trade negotiators missed the April 30 deadline for completing modalities in agriculture and industrial tariffs, commerce secretary S.N. Menon said today.

 New Delhi, May 1: The government has sought clarification from mobile service provider Hutchison-Essar about the push-to-talk services it offered for nearly two months a couple of years ago to ascertain whether the service violated any licence terms and conditions.

 New Delhi, May 1: The Burman family has increased its stake in Punjab Tractors to 12.5 per cent by buying an additional 1 per cent from the open market in the last one month, which brings it closer to making the mandatory open offer for picking up the additional stake.

 Mumbai, May 1: All markets, including the Bombay Stock Exchange, National Stock Exchange, foreign exchange (forex), money and commodity markets remained closed today on account of Maharashtra day.




